Pretty Good Privacy Fundamentals : Keep your messages a secret.

This document serves the purpose of understanding conceptually PKIs based on PGP. 

It's important to have a good understanding of a Public Key Infastructure if I want to build one for my homies and I to use. I figured the best
way to do it is through implementing a PKI through Pretty Good Privacy. 

What I like about PGP: 
    - Each user manages their own digital certificates 
    - PGP was designed for users to take privacy in their own hands. 

How PGP Certificates work: 
    - Alice is the issuer
    - Alice's public key is the subject
    - Certificates are self-signed, can be signed by multiple people 

How validation works in PGP (Integrity):
    - We verify our public keys to each other. If the public key isn't compromised,
    our values of the key should match. 
    - Another example of validation would be an example of homie A, B, and C. 
    homie A sent homie B his public key. Homie B sends homie C the certificate of A signed w/ homie B's certificate.
    if homie C trusts B, then A is validated to C.  